u:\mathbb{R}^2\to \mathbb{R}
u(x,y)= e^{x\sin y}f(x-y)
f: \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}
\frac{\partial u}{\partial x}+\frac{\partial u}{\partial y}=(\sin y+x\cos y)u.
\frac{\partial u}{\partial x}=\sin y\cdot e^{x\sin y}f(x-y)+e^{x\sin y}\frac{\partial }{\partial x}f(x-y)
\frac{\partial u}{\partial x}=x\cos y\cdot e^{x\sin y}f(x-y)+e^{x\sin y}\frac{\partial }{\partial y}f(x-y).
*
\frac{\partial }{\partial y}f(x-y)=-\frac{\partial }{\partial x}f(x-y).\tag{$*$}
(*)
f(x-y)
f(g(x,y)),
g(x,y)=x-y.
\frac{\partial}{\partial y}f(g(x,y))=\frac{df(u)}{du}\cdot \frac{\partial g(x,y)}{\partial y},
-\frac{df(u)}{du}.
\frac{\partial}{\partial x}f(g(x,y))
